@page "/"

<PageTitle>EditorJsonProcessor Demo</PageTitle>

<h1>EditorJsonToHtmlConverter — Map Block Rendering</h1>
<p>This demo showcases the two rendering modes for <code>map</code> blocks produced by the EditorJS leaflet-map plugin.</p>

<div style="display: flex; gap: 1rem; margin-top: 1.5rem;">
    <a href="/embedded" style="flex: 1; display: block; padding: 1.5rem; border: 1px solid #dee2e6; border-radius: 6px; text-decoration: none; color: inherit; background: #fff;">
        <h3 style="margin: 0 0 0.5rem 0;">Embedded Mode</h3>
        <p style="margin: 0; color: #495057; font-size: 0.875rem;">
            Full resolved data (venues, spaces, POIs, activities with coordinates and geometry)
            is serialised as a child <code>&lt;script type="application/json"&gt;</code> element.
            The client renders immediately without API calls.
        </p>
    </a>
    <a href="/reference" style="flex: 1; display: block; padding: 1.5rem; border: 1px solid #dee2e6; border-radius: 6px; text-decoration: none; color: inherit; background: #fff;">
        <h3 style="margin: 0 0 0.5rem 0;">Reference Mode</h3>
        <p style="margin: 0; color: #495057; font-size: 0.875rem;">
            GUID references and map configuration are output as <code>data-*</code> attributes.
            The viewer JS discovers the container and fetches full data from mock API endpoints at runtime.
        </p>
    </a>
</div>
